frameDefinitions: A fire which burns and requires an emergency-type response.
Ambient conditions of temperature, precipitation, windiness, and sunniness pertain at a certain Place and Time.
The words in this frame involve an Undesirable_event which affects the Patient negatively.
A Fire burns Fuel, resulting in damage and possibly complete destruction of the Fuel.
An Entity undergoes some change (the Event) that is (or is construed as) punctual.
frameExamples: The first <t>calamity</t> was a disastrous trade war with Holland.
A fire that started on Saturday afternoon, the High Glade Fire - located on the Mendocino National Forest's Upper Lake Ranger District - continued to <t>burn</t> actively on Sunday.
This <t>happens</t> to me all the time.
